ee definition"</a>. Newton Ask a Scientist. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.newton.dep.anl.gov/askasci/bot00/bot00761.htm">the original</a> on 2013-12-06<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2014-10-05</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Tree+definition&amp;rft.pub=Newton+Ask+a+Scientist&amp;rft.au=Tokuhisa%2C+Jim&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newton.dep.anl.gov%2Faskasci%2Fbot00%2Fbot00761.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATree" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-Gschwantner,_Thomas_2009-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Gschwantner,_Thomas_2009_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Gschwantner,_Thomas_2009_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Gschwantner,_Thomas_2009_4-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Gschwantner, Thomas, et al. "Common tree definitions for national forest inventories in Europe." <i>Silva Fennica</i> 43.2 (2009): 303–321.</span></li> <li id="cite_note-treedictionary-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-treedictionary_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-treedictionary_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-treedictionary_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Keslick, John A. (2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.treedictionary.com/">"Tree Biology Dictionary"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-07-30</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Tree+Biology+Dictionary&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.au=Keslick%2C+John+A.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.t